rmanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Rawlins was born in 1555, in Warminster, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Willimus Rawlins, was 17 and his mother, Alicia Pruitt, was 20. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sarah Mufet. He died on 13 August 1637, in his hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1555–13 Aug 1637":"1555–13. august 1637","1555–1637":"1555–1637","1560–1644":"1560–1644","1582–1635":"1582–1635","1585–1687":"1585–1687","1538–1557":"1538–1557","1535–1606":"1535–1606","1582":"1582","1560":"1560","Abt 1555":"umbes 1555","13 Aug 1637":"13. august 1637","1635":"1635","1557":"1557","1535":"1535","1644":"1644","1555":"1555","1687":"1687","1582 or 1590":"1582","1585":"1585","1606":"1606","1538":"1538","1637":"1637","Warminster, Wiltshire, England":"Warminster, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of St.Deny's, Warminster, Wiltshire, England":"Warminster, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Great Bedwyn, Wiltshire, England":"Great Bedwyn, Wiltshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Salisbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Salisbury, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St. Andrew's, Holborn, Middlesex, England":"Saint Andrew, Holborn, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1555–13 Aug 1637":"1555–13. elokuuta 1637","1555–1637":"1555–1637","1560–1644":"1560–1644","1582–1635":"1582–1635","1585–1687":"1585–1687","1538–1557":"1538–1557","1535–1606":"1535–1606","1582":"1582","1560":"1560","Abt 1555":"noin 1555","13 Aug 1637":"13. elokuuta 1637","